message: Kikongo has never been one of the four national languages in the Democratic Republic of Congo, either during Belgian colonization or after colonization. Kikongo ya leta (also called Kikongo in the former Bandundu (present Kwilu, Kwango and Mai Ndombe provinces) and in Kinshasa) was and is one of the four national languages. Therefore he was not protesting against slavery as a whole, but against Portuguese disrespect for local laws.
